        conclusion.</p>

        <h2>10 Ways to Avoid Plagiarism in Your Research Paper</h2>

        <h3>1. Understand How to Not Plagiarize When 
        Paraphrasing</h3>

        <p>Paraphrasing is more than just swapping out words for 
        synonyms. To paraphrase properly, fully digest the author's 
        argument and explain it using your own unique sentence 
        patterns and vocabulary. A helpful technique is to read the 
        source text, close the tab, explain the concept out loud, 
        and then write it from memory.</p>

        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Original Text</th>
              <th>Poor Paraphrase</th>
              <th>Acceptable Paraphrase</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>The integration of AI tools in higher education 
              has transformed traditional assessment methods.</td>
              <td>The implementation of AI software in college has 
